Nigeria Arrests 58 Suspects After Police Compound Explosion, Vanguard Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-06-20T08:11:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-20/nigeria-arrests-58-suspects-after-police-compound-explosion-vanguard-says.html
Nigerian police arrest 58 suspected
Boko Haram members in connection with an explosion in the
compound of the police headquarters in the capital, Abuja, on
June 16,  Vanguard  newspaper reported, without saying how it got
the information.  The government also asked the embassies of  Somalia ,  Sudan 
and  Niger  to provide comprehensive lists of their nationals
residing in the country after Somalis and Sudanese were among
those arrested, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 